        "subject": "Civil Law",
        "No": 391,
        "Question": "Plutarco owns land adjoining a river. If the river dries up, may Plutarco validly claim ownership over the dried-up river bed? Explain your answer. ",
        "Answer": "No, if the river dries up, Plutarco may not validly claim ownership over the dried-up river bed because **a river bed is property of public dominion and remains property of the State** (Article 420, Civil Code)."
