        "No": 444,
        "Question": "May Mr. A validly foreclose on the real estate mortgage even without prior demand to Mr. B? Explain. ",
        "Answer": "Yes, Mr. A may validly foreclose the mortgage even without prior demand. The law provides that demand is not necessary to put the debtor in delay when the **obligation expressly so declares** (Article 1169, Civil Code). In the present case, **Mr. B waived prior demand** in the promissory note, which secured the mortgage obligation."
