        "subject": "Civil Law",
        "No": 528,
        "Question": "Mahuhay Elementary School organized a fieldtrip for its Grade VI students. Parents signed a waiver. Joey, a 7-year-old student, was bitten by a snake. Was there a valid waiver of right to sue the school? Why?",
        "Answer": "No, there was no valid waiver of the right to sue the school. A waiver to be valid must not be contrary to law, morals, good customs, public order or public policy. The waiver may be considered contrary to public policy as it exonerates the school from liability for future negligence."
