        "Question": "Even if the applicable law is a foreign law, a court in the Philippines may be constrained to apply Philippine law under any of the following instances, except: A) When the foreign law, judgment or contract is contrary to a sound and important public policy of the forum; B) When the property subject of the case is located outside of the Philippines; C) When the foreign law or judgment is penal in nature; D) When the foreign law is procedural in nature.",
        "Answer": "B) When the property subject of the case is located outside of the Philippines."
