        "Question": "What is now the age of doli incapax in the Philippines?  (2017 BAR EXAM)",
        "Answer": "If the accused is 15 years of age or below, minority is an exempting circumstance (Section 6 of RA No. 9344). With or without discernment, the accused of such age is exempt from criminal liability. Lack of discernment is conclusively presumed. Hence, the age of doli incapax in the Philippines is now 15 years of age or under."
