        "Question": "RR convinced WW to take a job in Taiwan, assuring her of a good salary... WW paid to RR the processing fee... WW was made to use the alien certificate of registration of another person... The application of WW was rejected... The case of illegal recruitment was dismissed. Is RR liable for estafa?  a) RR is liable for estafa with unfaithfulness or abuse of confidence. b) RR is liable for estafa by means of false pretenses. c) RR is not liable for estafa because WW participated in the illegal travel documents. d) RR can no longer be held liable for estafa because with the dismissal of the case against him for illegal recruitment, double jeopardy has already set in.",
