        "Question": "A, B, C and D are members of the police department of a municipality. Conspiring with one another, they arrested E, without reasonable ground, for the purpose of delivering him to the proper authorities by imputing to E the crime of bribery. While E was being investigated... one of them placed a marked five hundred peso bill... to make it appear that E... agreed to perform an act not constituting a crime in connection with the performance of E's duties... What is the crime committed by A, B, C and D?  a) A, B, C and D committed incriminatory machination through unlawful arrest. b) A, B, C and D committed intriguing against honor with unlawful arrest. c) A, B, C and D committed slight illegal detention. d) A, B, C and D committed corruption of public official.",
