        "Question": "How much attorney's fees may a lawyer assess a culpable party in cases of unlawful withholding of wages?",
        "Answer": "In cases of unlawful withholding of wages, the culpable party may be assessed attorney's fees equivalent to ten percent (10%) of the amount of wages recovered. (Art. III, Labor Code)"
