        "Answer": "It is not enough to show substantial capitalization or investment in the form of tools, equipment, machinery and work premises. In addition, the following factors have to be considered: (a) whether the contractor is carrying on an independent business; (f) the control and supervision of the workers; (g) the power of employer with respect to the hiring, firing and payment of workers of the contractor."
