        "Answer": "The completion of the house should be valid cause for termination of Diosdado’s employment. Although the employment contract may not state a particular date, but if it did specify that the termination of the parties' employment relationship was to be on a 'day certain' - the day when the phase of work would be completed - the employee cannot be considered to have been a regular employee. To satisfy due process requirement, under DOLE Department Order No. 19, series of 1993, the employer is required to report to the relevant DOLE Regional Office the fact of termination of project employees as a result of the completion of the project or any phase thereof in which one is employed."
