        "Answer": "NO. The management is not correct. The inclusion in a union of disqualified employees is not a ground for cancellation of union registration. The inclusion of the probationary staff, the casuals, and the employees of the landscape contractor simply makes the aforementioned employees automatically deemed removed from the union membership [Art. 245-A, Labor Code]."
