        "Answer": "The tax benefit that may be obtained by Henry and the buyer from the sale-leaseback transaction is the deduction from gross income of the rental payments by Henry as business expense and the deduction from gross income of the buyer of the expenses incurred in the maintenance and operation of the property. However, the sale of the property by Henry to the buyer is subject to income tax on the gain from the sale, if any, and the lease of the property by Henry from the buyer is subject to value-added tax (VAT) or percentage tax, as the case may be, and the income of the buyer from the lease is subject to income tax."
