        "Answer": "(A) All earnings from the practice of law are included in gross income. This includes acceptance fees, appearance fees, and notarization fees. Rentals, interest, and dividends are also included. (B) All ordinary and necessary expenses paid or incurred in carrying on the trade or business are deductible. This includes salaries, supplies, utilities, and rent. (C) The partnership itself is not subject to income tax. Instead, the net income is distributed to the partners and taxed at their individual rates."
