        "Answer": "The Motion to Dismiss is without merit and therefore should be denied. Courts of the first level have jurisdiction over civil actions where the demand is for sum of money not exceeding P300, 000.00 or in Metro-Manila, P400, 000.00, exclusive of Interest, damages, attorney's fees, litigation expenses and, costs: this jurisdiction includes admiralty and marine cases. And where the main cause of action is the claim for damages, the Amount thereof shall be considered in determining the jurisdiction of the court (Adm. Circular No. 09-94, June 14, 1994)."
