        "Question": "A complaint for collection of sum of money was filed by A against B before the MTC of Manila. The complaint was accompanied by a certification to file action issued by the Lupon Secretary of Barangay 123, Zone 12, District IV, Manila. The certification states that no conciliation or settlement was reached, hence the corresponding complaint for the dispute may now be filed in court. B filed a motion to dismiss the complaint on the ground of failure to state a cause of action because the certification to file action was issued by the Lupon Secretary and not by the Punong Barangay as required under Sec. 412(b)(1) of the Local Government Code. Is the motion to dismiss tenable? ",
