        "Question": "The deposition of a witness, whether or not a party, may be used for any purpose if the Court finds the following circumstances are attendant, EXCEPT:  a. when the witness is dead. b. when the witness is incarcerated. c. when the witness is outside the Philippines and absence is procured by the party offering deposition. d. when the witness is 89 years old and bed-ridden.",
