        "Question": "The Department of Agrarian Reform (DAR) issued Administrative Order (AO) No. 06-08, which provides that 'all agrarian law implementers (ALIs) shall undergo a mandatory training program on agrarian reform and social justice to be conducted by the DAR Academy.' The DAR Academy is a government-owned and -controlled corporation (GOCC) created by law to provide training and education on agrarian reform. The AO also provides that 'no ALI shall be promoted to a higher position unless he/she has completed the mandatory training program.' The League of Provincial Agrarian Reform Officers (LOPARO) filed a petition for prohibition with the Supreme Court, seeking to nullify AO No. 06-08 on the ground that it violates the principle of separation of powers. LOPARO argues that the power to prescribe qualifications for public office is legislative in nature, and cannot be delegated to an administrative agency. Decide with reasons. ",
