        "Answer": "The motion is not tenable. The power of the PCGG to prosecute cases involving the recovery of ill-gotten wealth is valid. The power to prosecute is executive in nature and is vested in the President. The President may delegate this power to the PCGG. The power of the Ombudsman to investigate and prosecute is not exclusive. It is shared with other agencies of government."
