        "Answer": "Under Section 23(2), Article VI of the Constitution, Congress may grant the President emergency powers subject to the following conditions: 1. There is a war or other national emergency; 2. The grant of emergency powers must be for a limited period; 3. The grant of emergency powers is subject to such restrictions as Congress may prescribe; and 4. The emergency powers must be exercised to carry out a declared national policy."
